# Windows: run Python scripts via python.exe

On **Windows**, do **not** invoke `.py` scripts directly (e.g. `build.py`, `env\bin\cit.py`). Run them as an argument to `python.exe`.

**Correct (Windows):**
```powershell
python build.py d
python env\bin\cit.py
python env\bin\cit.py -l
python env\bin\format-all-sources.py -d
```

**Incorrect (Windows):**
```powershell
build.py d
.\env\bin\cit.py
env\bin\cit.py -l
```

On Linux/WSL you may run scripts directly if they are executable and the shebang is set (e.g. `./build.py d`, `env/bin/cit.py`), but on Windows always use `python <script>.py`.
